Ravi Shankar Raju Bhupatiraju (born 26 January 1968), better known by the stage name Ravi Teja, is an Indian actor who predominantly works in Telugu cinema. Known for his roles in action comedy films, Teja has appeared in over 70 films and is one of the highest paid actors in Telugu film industry.[3][4] He won the Nandi Special Jury Award in 1999 and 2002 for his performance in the films Nee Kosam (1999) and Khadgam (2002) and also won the Nandi Award for Best Actor for Neninthe in 2008. He is known for his collaborations with director Puri Jagannadh which turned out to be major breakthroughs in his career. 
